The paper deals with algorithms for external memory data processing, which is a common topic in the data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. The focus on privacy and data access patterns suggests a potential fit for the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of new algorithmic techniques and data perturbation techniques suggests a potential fit for the algorithms and complexity (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the mention of oblivious RAM simulations suggests a potential fit for the computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
